            <description><![CDATA[Ever wondered how companies analyze thousands of customer reviews in seconds? In this post, I walk through building a real-time sentiment analysis application using HuggingFace Transformers, FastAPI, and Streamlit.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Ever wondered how companies analyze thousands of customer reviews in seconds? In this post, I walk through building a real-time sentiment analysis application using HuggingFace Transformers, FastAPI, and Streamlit.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-the-problem">ğŸ¯ The Problem<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#-the-problem" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ğŸ¯ The Problem" title="Direct link to ğŸ¯ The Problem" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>Understanding the emotional tone of text is crucial for:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>Customer feedback analysis</strong> - Quickly categorize reviews as positive or negative</li>
<li class=""><strong>Social media monitoring</strong> - Track brand sentiment in real-time</li>
<li class=""><strong>Market research</strong> - Gauge public opinion on products or services</li>
</ul>
<p>Manually analyzing text at scale is impossible. We need AI.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="ï¸-architecture-overview">ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture Overview<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#%EF%B8%8F-architecture-overview" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture Overview" title="Direct link to ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture Overview" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>The application follows a clean separation of concerns:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" alt="arch" src="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/assets/images/image-a91acdea4fbeb3af975cf066234a0fba.png" width="1153" height="631" class="img_ev3q"></p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="backend-fastapi">Backend (FastAPI)<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#backend-fastapi" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Backend (FastAPI)" title="Direct link to Backend (FastAPI)" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>The backend serves as the inference engine, exposing REST APIs for:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><code>/models</code> - List available sentiment models</li>
<li class=""><code>/predict</code> - Perform sentiment classification</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="frontend-streamlit">Frontend (Streamlit)<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#frontend-streamlit" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Frontend (Streamlit)" title="Direct link to Frontend (Streamlit)" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>A clean, interactive UI where users can:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Enter text for analysis</li>
<li class="">Select multiple models for comparison</li>
<li class="">View predictions with confidence scores</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="ml-models-huggingface">ML Models (HuggingFace)<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#ml-models-huggingface" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ML Models (HuggingFace)" title="Direct link to ML Models (HuggingFace)" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>The app supports multiple pre-trained models:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>DistilBERT</strong> - Lightweight and fast</li>
<li class=""><strong>BERTweet</strong> - Optimized for social media text</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-key-features">ğŸš€ Key Features<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#-key-features" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ğŸš€ Key Features" title="Direct link to ğŸš€ Key Features" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="real-time-predictions">Real-Time Predictions<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#real-time-predictions" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Real-Time Predictions" title="Direct link to Real-Time Predictions" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>Users get instant feedback as they type. The models classify text into:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">âœ… <strong>Positive</strong> - Expresses satisfaction or happiness</li>
<li class="">âŒ <strong>Negative</strong> - Expresses dissatisfaction or frustration</li>
<li class="">âšª <strong>Neutral</strong> - Factual statements without emotional charge</li>
<li class="">ğŸ”„ <strong>Mixed</strong> - Contains both positive and negative sentiments</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="confidence-scores">Confidence Scores<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#confidence-scores" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Confidence Scores" title="Direct link to Confidence Scores" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>Each prediction comes with a confidence percentage, helping users understand the model's certainty.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="multi-model-comparison">Multi-Model Comparison<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#multi-model-comparison" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Multi-Model Comparison" title="Direct link to Multi-Model Comparison" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>Compare predictions from different models side-by-side. This is especially useful for:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Understanding model strengths and weaknesses</li>
<li class="">Validating predictions across architectures</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-example-use-cases">ğŸ’¡ Example Use Cases<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#-example-use-cases" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ğŸ’¡ Example Use Cases" title="Direct link to ğŸ’¡ Example Use Cases" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>Try these sample inputs to see the app in action:</p>
<div class="language-text codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">I absolutely love this product! It exceeded my expectations.</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">â†’ Positive (High Confidence)</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">This is the worst experience I've ever had.</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">â†’ Negative (High Confidence)</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">The package arrived yesterday.</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">â†’ Neutral (Medium Confidence)</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">The movie started off boring but ended with an amazing twist.</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">â†’ Mixed (Model-dependent)</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="financial-sentiment-analysis">Financial Sentiment Analysis<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#financial-sentiment-analysis" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Financial Sentiment Analysis" title="Direct link to Financial Sentiment Analysis" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>The app also handles domain-specific text like financial news:</p>
<div class="language-text codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">Revenue increased in North America but sharp losses in </span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">European markets offset most of the gains.</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">â†’ Mixed/Neutral</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-running-locally">ğŸ”§ Running Locally<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#-running-locally" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ğŸ”§ Running Locally" title="Direct link to ğŸ”§ Running Locally" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>Clone and set up the project:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">git clone https://github.com/vinaykagithapu/sentiment-analysis-app.git</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">cd sentiment-analysis-app</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain"># Backend setup</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">python -m venv .venv-be</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">source .venv-be/bin/activate</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">pip install -r backend/requirements.txt</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">export HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN=&lt;your_token&gt;</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">uvicorn backend.main:app --reload --port 8000</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain"># Frontend setup (new terminal)</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">python -m venv .venv-fe</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">source .venv-fe/bin/activate</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">pip install -r frontend/requirements.txt</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">streamlit run frontend/app.py</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="ï¸-kubernetes-deployment">â˜¸ï¸ Kubernetes Deployment<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#%EF%B8%8F-kubernetes-deployment" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to â˜¸ï¸ Kubernetes Deployment" title="Direct link to â˜¸ï¸ Kubernetes Deployment" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>The project includes Kubernetes manifests for production deployment. This makes it easy to:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Scale horizontally based on demand</li>
<li class="">Deploy in any cloud environment</li>
<li class="">Implement health checks and rolling updates</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-future-improvements">ğŸ”® Future Improvements<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#-future-improvements" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ğŸ”® Future Improvements" title="Direct link to ğŸ”® Future Improvements" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>I'm planning to add:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>GPU optimization</strong> for faster inference</li>
<li class=""><strong>Multi-language support</strong> beyond English</li>
<li class=""><strong>Batch processing</strong> for analyzing large datasets</li>
<li class=""><strong>Cloud deployment</strong> for public access</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-conclusion">ğŸ‰ Conclusion<a href="https://vinaykagithapu.github.io/blog/sentiment-analysis-app/#-conclusion" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ğŸ‰ Conclusion" title="Direct link to ğŸ‰ Conclusion" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>Building this project reinforced my understanding of:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Serving ML models in production environments</li>
<li class="">Designing clean API interfaces</li>
<li class="">Creating intuitive user experiences for AI applications</li>
</ul>
<p>Check out the full source code on <a href="https://github.com/vinaykagithapu/sentiment-analysis-app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">GitHub</a> and feel free to contribute!</p>
